vices to broker-dealers; exchange-traded funds; advisory solutions for managed portfolios, separately managed accounts, customized personal advice for tailored portfolios, specialized planning, and full-time portfolio management; banking products comprising checking and savings accounts, first lien residential real estate mortgage loans, home equity lines of credit, and pledged asset lines; and trust custody services, personal trust reporting services, and administrative trustee services. It provides digital and software based trading platforms; research tools, and multichannel support, real-time market data, options trading; equity compensation plan sponsors full-service recordkeeping for stock plans, stock options, restricted stock, performance shares, and stock appreciation rights; retirement plan services; mutual fund clearing services; and advisor services, including interactive tools and educational content. The Company operates through branch offices. The Charles Schwab Corporation was founded in 1971 and is headquartered in Westlake, Texas.","industry":"Capital Markets","sector":"Financial Services","marketCap":152817844224,"trailingPE":17.469185,"forwardPE":12.172165,"pegRatio":1.07,"priceToBook":3.5960715,"priceToSales":6.161016,"profitMargin":37.986,"operatingMargin":49.352002,"grossMargin":97.46000000000001,"returnOnEquity":19.083,"returnOnAssets":1.9709998999999998,"revenueGrowthYoy":15.8,"earningsGrowthYoy":38.6,"earningsQuarterlyGrowthYoy":29.9,"debtToEquity":120.766,"currentRatio":0.632,"quickRatio":0.632,"freeCashFlow":null,"operatingCashFlow":10293999616,"totalCash":96474996736,"totalDebt":59457998848,"revenue":24803999744,"dividendYield":1.47,"payoutRatio":22.469998999999998,"beta":0.797,"fiftyTwoWeekHigh":107.5,"fiftyTwoWeekLow":83.96,"targetMeanPrice":115.85,"targetHighPrice":137,"targetLowPrice":84,"recommendationKey":"buy","numberOfAnalystOpinions":20,"lastQuarter":{"date":"2026-03-31","period":"-1q","epsActual":1.43,"epsEstimate":1.39538,"sur